<TITLE> Dhaka Int'l Trade Fair opens Thursday </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 31(bdnews24.com)  President Iajuddin Ahmed is set to launch Dhaka International Trade Fair-2009 at Bangladesh-China Friendship Conference Centre at 10am on Thursday. The month-long fair will have five special pavilions, four premium pavilions, 52 general pavilions, two premier mini-pavilions, 45 mini-pavilions, 312 general stalls and 12 restaurants, Export Promotion Bureau vice chairman Shahabul Alam said. Twelve countries including the United States, Japan, China, Sri Lanka, Singapore, Thailand, India and Pakistan will participate in the fair. Adequate security steps have taken for the fair, he said at a press conference at his office at Karwan Bazar. About Tk 7.5 crore will be spent on the fair. The amount spent in 2008 and 2006 was over Tk 6.46 crore and Tk 5.90 crore respectively, he disclosed. Entry fee for the fair is Tk 12 for visitors beyond the age of 12 years and Tk 7 for 3-12-year olds. Asked why the entry fee has been raised, he said, "Entry fee this time has been raised as the prices of construction materials have gone up." Entry fee for the adults was Tk 10 and for those below 12 years it was Tk 5. bdnews24
